        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Google has a number of approaches to indexing paywalled content. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Lead-in",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With this option, the reader sees a snippet of the whole article, while the rest remains blocked to non-paying members. Google indexes the snippet alone and make ranking decisions based on that. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Metered",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Google has a strong preference for metered paywalls, which allow it to index all content. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "These both fall under Google's flexible sampling policy, which you can read here:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/7532484?hl=en",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/7532484?hl=en",
          "title": "Flexible Sampling general guidance - Search Console Help",
          "description": "Allow limited free access to your site; help Google crawl paywalled contentIn order to better understand the potential impact of free sampling changes on Google users and publishersâ€™ subscription mo",
          "author": null,
          "publisher": "Search Console Help",
          "thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/iyJZOYB-OnYWs0GqA-QFmBPpjL0PJMB-XyfpVu95XL4xqzCh5XU7ZQdUMWAzmHvaIqI=w512",
          "icon": null
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "If you're unwilling or unable to go that route, the other option is to find a system that allows Googlebot (the search crawler) to see the content as it it was a member - but use markup to indicate to Google that it's paywalled content, so you don't fall foul of Google's ban on cloaking. There's a developer article explaining ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "how to implement this in structured data",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://developers.google.com/search/docs/data-types/paywalled-content",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Google is philosophically happy to show people paywalled content in search results, as this story shows:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
